    "causal_summary": "The 5 CLI orchestrator skills (`cli-claude-code`, `cli-codex`, `cli-gemini`, `cli-opencode`) currently mention specific overlay skills (`sk-code-review`, `sk-code-opencode`) by name when describing how dispatched sessions should load code-quality standards. This is brittle: the moment a different stack is in play (Webflow, React/Next.js, Go) the dispatch prompt instructs the dispatched session to load the wrong overlay.",
